what age did you potty train your toddler how did you do it mostly for a girl one of my sons potty trained himself before he was two he's three now and it was nice to not have to buy pull ups anymore his older brother was at least three before we could get him out of pull ups i don't have a lot of advice in getting girls out of diapers other than the basics of don't make it a bad thing a lot of parents scold their toddlers for accidents or for not using the toilet that tends to make it worse instead of better praise her when she does use the potty or get through a night without wetting her pull up but keep in mind if she's still not getting through the night without a wet diaper she is not ready yet that's the first thing to look for when potty training Kimberly-Clark Corporation Rugrats Elimination communication Diaper Toilet training Infantilism Urinary incontinence Parenting The Fairly OddParents Humphrey Bogart Fecal incontinence Bedwetting The Sims 2 The Girl Who Slept Too Little One Tree Hill (TV series) Future-Drama The Isley Brothers Avenue Q On A Clear Day I Can't See My Sister Social rule Captain Underpants Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Miss Saigon Genericized trademark EastEnders Toilet humour The Sims The Contender (television series) Shaggy dog story The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Feral child Toilet paper Theory of conduct 50 First Dates Puni Puni Poemy The Chemical Brothers Housebreaking Masturbation Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Time Out of Mind Toilet Conker's Bad Fur Day Japanese toilet YuYu Hakusho Ranma __ characters Ranma Saotome Cruising (maritime) Recess (TV series) FoxTrot The Catcher in the Rye Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Mad Money Kimi Finster Joy (novel) Dog training Married... with Children Milton H. Erickson The Lovely Bones Harold & Kumar Go to White Castle Fiddler on the Roof Great Teacher Onizuka Sin City John Lennon Self Portrait Biff Tannen Russian 